<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7035335>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Zygophylax biarmata Billard, 1905. A, two colonies; B, hydrocaulus with coppinia; C, hydrothecal arrangement along a hydrocladium; D, an axillary hydrotheca (arrow); E, a hydrotheca with diaphragm (left arrow) and basal nematotheca (right arrow); F, magnification of a nematotheca; G, distal part of a hydrotheca showing multiple renovations. From samples: A–G: ZSM 20220294, Gulf of Cadiz. A, B, D, E, light microscope images; C, F, G, SEM images. Scale bars: A, B = 2 mm; C = 200 µm; D = 500 µm; E = 100 µm; F, G = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7035335/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

